> Any callback is a GOTO. in fact, any function call in C like languages IS A GOTO.<p>If a function call would be a GOTO, then you wouldn&#x27;t have a stack trace to look at in your debugger.<p>I&#x27;m not sure what is the point in replying to a comment you don&#x27;t actually understand.<p>Angular&#x27;s data binding model has a lot of shortcomings:<p><pre><code>    angular.module(&quot;app&quot;).controller(&quot;SomeController&quot;, function($scope) {
       setTimeout(function () {
           $scope.someVar = &#x27;happy debugging&#x27;;
       }, 500);
   });</code></pre>
